From 83b513c2f69ff526215e3251a6450d5e739372ac Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ripan Deuri <quic_rdeuri@quicinc.com>
Date: Fri, 21 Mar 2025 14:05:34 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/8] wifi: ath12k: Convert ath12k_dp member in ath12k_base to
 pointer

With Unified Driver framework, the Data Path (DP) speficic device object
(ath12k_dp) need to support different hardware architectures. Keeping DP
structure as a pointer makes it dynamic and thus the allocation and
initialization is done as per the underlying hardware architecture.

In this change, convert ath12k_dp member in ath12k_base to a pointer,
enabling hardware-dependent allocations. This flexibility is essential for
future enhancements and hardware-specific initializations.

This patch (and the forthcoming patches) are intended to serve the purpose
of refactoring DP objects for the Unified Driver framework.

Tested-on: QCN9274 hw2.0 PCI WLAN.WBE.1.3.1-00173-QCAHKSWPL_SILICONZ-1
Tested-on: WCN7850 hw2.0 PCI WLAN.HMT.1.0.c5-00481-QCAHMTSWPL_V1.0_V2.0_SILICONZ-3

Signed-off-by: Ripan Deuri <quic_rdeuri@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Harsh Kumar Bijlani <quic_hbijlani@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Aman Mehta <quic_amanmeht@quicinc.com>
